-- Erste’s BCR Lends $21 Million to Espe for Romanian Power Plant
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2012-07-25T09:30:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/erste-s-bcr-lends-21-million-to-espe-for-romanian-power-plant.html
Banca Comerciala Romana SA,
Romania’s largest bank, lent 17 million euros ($21 million) to
 Italy ’s  Espe Srl ’s unit to help finance the construction of a
hydroelectric plant in the Balkan country.  Espe will invest 23 million euros in the 9.9-megawatt plant
to be located on the Sapanta river in the Maramures region, the
bank, known as BCR, said in an e-mailed statement today.  “The portfolio of renewable energy projects approved by
BCR has a combined capacity of more than 100 megawatts,
consisting mostly of wind and small hydroelectric plants
projects,” Ioana Gheorghiade, project finance executive
director at BCR, said in the statement.  Bucharest-based BCR is a unit of Austria’s  Erste Group Bank
